02/21/84  attach_lv, alv

Syntax:  alv volume_name


Function: attaches a logical volume to the caller's process.


Arguments:
volume_name
   specifies the name of the logical volume to be attached.


Notes: A logical volume (unless it is a public logical volume) must be
attached for each process that wants to use it.  In order for a logical
volume to be attached it must first be physically mounted.  To attach
a logical volume you must have rw access to it.
